[thinking] I'm thinking about the agent exploring the Hibernate package. I wonder if it will need hibernate-core since normal library usage might include optional integrations, not just core functionalities. It feels like we shouldn't add broad optional dependencies unless absolutely necessary. The existing build excludes Hibernate, even though there seems to be coverage with BeanUtils in hibernate.management.impl. But it raises the question of how to compile since that class doesn’t import Hibernate. Other classes would need it, but tests don’t cover this.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Investigating JMS and BTM**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm looking into the existing build which includes `org.apache.geronimo.specs:geronimo-jms_1.1_spec:1.1.1` and BTM. I wonder why JMS is involved here. It’s possible that BTM relies on JMS interfaces, but maybe they aren’t transitive? I also notice that `DefaultTransactionManagerLookup` has factories specifically for Bitronix. It seems important to inspect the imports further to clarify how everything connects. That should help in understanding the dependencies better!
[thinking] 
