BTM. I wonder why JMS is involved here. It’s possible that BTM relies on JMS interfaces, but maybe they aren’t transitive? I also notice that `DefaultTransactionManagerLookup` has factories specifically for Bitronix. It seems important to inspect the imports further to clarify how everything connects. That should help in understanding the dependencies better!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_051837fa0b267e4c016a430995b94481969e97dba3a80a1f22\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQwmoHTOgaiwYe6udM2hkIVYxFfI0_dA-X1EmY5OXJaNeJoVYUz_lSXxZ7ZfsYAiI7B4wI84Fv_ZMoQvfcqvnq4WfnR-3rB-dHYQGODScGA-p0bA2XSBeds-X2uUI118jEz4roSPzkg7fEXJ39ke-2L49hN8ZHmfUD95oZeijqyKf6_7LvJP_0bID4oRQevYOHXucRov4WU1hPXSFn_XzRzNlHp8Mag8vW5rtSdknLgFrCzAvIgr1nw3E6yqAjFgB4MS00sT0d0iERRmIBRULdiM2MD8STt8ZBpOsXj_PYAEzNl50_faF6y6Wk4Kqau3G1mc-9z6Ad484xtD4x0CH4quWwNLiN8Qx3jCeTlGz1pzVCjM2yRW5fsc9KWr6_O1Xl6piYw1j477jQNqRLNr7F-NEzmzj2gnisKX2EfSrE_Cxg56z4XeA4giSpo8vxyLUpAlrgoybhpQ2qqe228SbA6gWvhrlmoVvcqj2EEPo02ZGDLkNG9SL3CTxzvwtOIFYu00PFNKUFCTuWRgPMbkWxB726I3Sc8SVAeMFjbWwio9i7uZXgEVCLkoGMCgdMTc0AFR8ZNCk1aycp4u2o9IRtpvkb-0QZwCYWw0HExDgmfH4Vgj0sU-sTFupdl5rYIswKrYEjjJ9YoAmzdCszRkcgz06WAiYJsNwtU5EC7JYjoN76XN_bIvSPtRTV4TebxQCfbIDLLebexwZYC0JXwXCRdMe8tCYux7BjuxKTapPx4F-6r7ysUxdPSXuBl3he5qYyNjM7cvL3pOLJ7-mjqFZufA2S0AG93mjwGyn_a8Yu2wwU5V0ib0azjFeX0HhAzzTUFwgP9WGJLTmHF86RA83Tq6PnxjrsfXbueWC79WxiGGgr-oZnBRW3tqLgNenkQBTTkl_0Fao4UL1ldisbbz8MAPFmSv7kRUeQXsVegUwznb_TGdD-q3HYpM4iFegguHyIYAarAWsbexJ2zDkWTQamHwF_TS5RwTdfJ5hvb3AlrUkJwaODPCewJykBO94Qph0Ae8l_HZyRKgNVPX0BbK7hPuCD4bXa_hMAJsRh3ACbtp3DodRqbKSkPQWPDqL3B204sOE6OPoeI9FxnntgZqgHP6F_8BbC4xL-J5HKST7KmgrMH2z-0DnlJxjsOGBhSmgfim0KuqQDrzXhbfFAw1AcoEpmlxY4Qi6dj7OQQ817pwgaCeTy_SUP7wThXQf519KD2Vbry20w7v354lg32taZaV2X6pL6-9k67Or9fZRCHrN6SGpPIISPmL3dlJbi_7hLfpvHDcNCLWwoEleKh5fmHf2J00Q3HzDnOyjSVoqcaHXnDpKa8vOub8alZB2MpLw_ELfQdfNQG7kL7S4XjCW1mT-fkjkD_ljUB-B_qN-IsxeVEaayqp--91xaq1Lh68-U_6B0G4HDR7WO264T8Yd03uMtP3pToZnGaaFWA0LloXQz5-ygC4MQOIEoCB4kMCCm-oWES